* Race: Draenei.
* Guild: Nightfall.
* Realm: Moonglade.

[http://eu.wowarmory.com/character-sheet.xml?r=Moonglade&n=Kaimei A link to his Armory Page, which no longer works because the file is not found.]

From the armory page, and general observation of his character, it should become obvious Ryan is taking WoW far too seriously. He has, apparently, managed to gloat himself into one of the top end raiding guilds of the server, and has been there for only a few months. The time preceeding this prestegious status, he spent in a casual guild, where basically everybody that is shit at WoW reside, and enjoy getting mocked accordingly by the better players. Furthermore, Ryan only apears to have excelled himself and finding 24 other people to "boost" him through raiding content, which is generally regarded as the ''skillless'' side to WoW. His Player vs. Player achievments are somewhat lacking.

He has, of course, been staking great claims with regards to WoW, boasting about his three "full T3 characters," many "Legendary" quality items and his overall supremacy over all other players. In an unfortunate turn of events, Ryan's 6-week coma spell left him incapacitated and unable to play WoW for a full two days.
